gujarati.context:
Here is the translation:

Whatever got happiness will become big in it, that only remains in Dharm; 
It is said in Sruti-Smriti like this, how can Truth-Dharm be bound?

Here is the translation:

This having said, patience was given to me; grief's cord was cut by my master; 
After that, a wave arose there which had an extremely sweet taste, like water with a hint of sweetness.

Here is the translation:

When I see another Brahmin, my mind becomes firmly decided; 
This is a great sage of valor, when I see him, my soul has become lowly with you.
